cs.GT, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CC. 

This paper deals with the computational complexity of manipulating voting systems, which is a topic in computational social choice. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Decision Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as likely sub-categories. The paper's focus on voting systems and the use of scoring protocols suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as possible sub-categories as well.
